WEBVTT

00:02.419 --> 00:04.754
- IT'S THE OPENING SOLO,
BABY.

00:04.838 --> 00:08.550
YOU HAVE GOT TO PUT MORE POWER
IN YOUR PERFORMANCE.

00:08.633 --> 00:10.802
NOW, JUST BECAUSE
IT'S A HYMN ABOUT HUMILITY

00:10.885 --> 00:15.473
DOES NOT MEAN THAT YOU
CAN'T GRAB THE SPOTLIGHT.

00:17.350 --> 00:19.644
- "HEY, MOM, LET'S CARPOOL
TO CHOIR PRACTICE.

00:19.728 --> 00:21.271
IT'LL BE FUN."

00:21.354 --> 00:22.480
SEPARATE CARS.

00:22.564 --> 00:24.524
ALWAYS TAKE
SEPARATE CARS.

00:24.607 --> 00:26.526
- WHAT WAS THAT?

00:26.609 --> 00:28.069
- NOTHING.

00:28.153 --> 00:29.028
- SEE?

00:29.112 --> 00:30.321
YOU'RE TWO FEET AWAY
FROM ME,

00:30.405 --> 00:32.949
AND I CAN'T HEAR
A WORD YOU'RE SAYING.

00:33.032 --> 00:35.910
HONEY,
YOU HAVE GOT TO PROJECT.

00:35.994 --> 00:37.370
MAKE YOUR VOICE CLEAR

00:37.454 --> 00:40.123
SO PEOPLE CAN UNDERSTAND
YOUR MESSAGE.

00:40.206 --> 00:42.000
- IS THIS CLEAR ENOUGH?

00:42.083 --> 00:47.881
♪ GO HOME ♪

00:50.800 --> 00:53.803
[wailing guitar solo]

00:53.887 --> 00:55.847
♪ ♪

00:55.930 --> 01:00.477
- THANK YOU,
PHILADELPHIA!

01:00.560 --> 01:04.272
T-SHIRTS FOR SALE
IN THE LOBBY!

01:04.355 --> 01:08.234
- YOU REALLY SHOULD START
DRUG-TESTING THAT CHILD.

01:08.318 --> 01:12.697
- WOW, YOU'RE GETTING
REALLY GOOD AT THAT.

01:12.781 --> 01:14.949
- I BETTER BE GOOD IF I'M GONNA
MAKE IT AS A MUSICIAN.

01:15.033 --> 01:17.202
AND IF I'M GONNA PLAY CLUBS,

01:17.285 --> 01:21.289
WE'LL PROBABLY NEED A LOUDER TV
TO SHOWCASE MY TALENT.

01:21.372 --> 01:22.540
- OH.

01:22.624 --> 01:23.666
WELL, I DON'T THINK
PLAYING <i> GUITAR IDOL</i>

01:23.750 --> 01:25.043
MAKES YOU A MUSICIAN.

01:25.126 --> 01:28.213
- DO YOU PLAY
ANY REAL INSTRUMENTS?

01:28.296 --> 01:32.008
- WHAT,
LIKE "VIOLIN IDOL"?

01:32.091 --> 01:33.676
HEY, ROCKING OUT'S
MAKING ME HUNGRY.

01:33.760 --> 01:35.011
CAN I HAVE A SNACK?

01:35.094 --> 01:36.012
- HAVE A PIECE OF FRUIT.

01:36.095 --> 01:37.096
- THAT STUFF'S FAKE.

01:37.180 --> 01:38.389
- SO IS YOUR TALENT.

01:40.099 --> 01:43.019
[funky music]

01:43.102 --> 01:47.440
♪ ♪

01:47.524 --> 01:48.358
- ♪ YEAH ♪

01:48.441 --> 01:54.447
♪ ♪

01:54.531 --> 01:56.449
- ♪ HUH, HUH-HUH, HUH ♪

01:56.533 --> 01:58.368
♪ HUH, HUH-HUH, HUH ♪

01:58.451 --> 02:00.411
♪ HUH, HUH-HUH, HUH ♪

02:00.495 --> 02:02.539
♪ HUH-HUH ♪
- ♪ YEAH ♪

02:02.622 --> 02:04.499
- ♪ HUH, HUH-HUH, HUH ♪

02:04.582 --> 02:06.459
♪ HUH, HUH-HUH, HUH ♪

02:06.543 --> 02:07.877
♪ HUH, HUH-HUH, HUH ♪

02:07.961 --> 02:09.586
- ♪ OOH, OOH, OOH ♪

02:14.592 --> 02:16.219
{\an8}- THE DOCTOR
WILL SEE YOU NOW.

02:19.305 --> 02:22.058
{\an8}OOH, SO TENSE.

02:22.141 --> 02:25.895
{\an8}I'LL HAVE TO RUN
A FULL DIAGNOSTIC.

02:25.979 --> 02:29.357
{\an8}YOU KNOW, I DON'T USUALLY
TAKE YOUR TYPE OF INSURANCE,

02:29.440 --> 02:32.402
{\an8}BUT IN YOUR CASE...

02:32.485 --> 02:33.945
{\an8}COME ON.

02:34.028 --> 02:37.991
{\an8}DON'T YOU WANT TO PLAY DOCTOR
WITH AN ACTUAL DOCTOR?

02:38.074 --> 02:41.244
{\an8}- HONEY, WHY WOULD YOU
BUY JAMES <i> GUITAR IDOL?</i>

02:41.327 --> 02:43.079
{\an8}- ARE WE GONNA TALK
ABOUT THE KIDS NOW?

02:43.162 --> 02:44.289
{\an8}'CAUSE I MAY AS WELL
PUT ON MY BATHROBE.

02:44.372 --> 02:46.124
{\an8}- I MEAN,
I DON'T KNOW WHAT'S WORSE,

02:46.207 --> 02:49.711
{\an8}THAT HE NEVER PLAYED
A REAL INSTRUMENT

02:49.794 --> 02:51.629
{\an8}OR THAT I AGREED
WITH MY MOTHER.

02:51.713 --> 02:53.339
{\an8}- OH, WE'RE TALKING
ABOUT YOUR MOTHER NOW?

02:53.423 --> 02:54.507
{\an8}PUTTING ON THE SHOES.

02:56.843 --> 02:59.095
{\an8}JAMES NEVER SHOWED ANY INTEREST
IN AN INSTRUMENT.

02:59.178 --> 03:00.221
{\an8}NONE OF THEM EVER HAVE.

03:00.305 --> 03:01.931
{\an8}- THAT'S CRAZY.

03:02.015 --> 03:04.183
{\an8}I STARTED VOICE LESSONS
WHEN I WAS SIX.

03:04.267 --> 03:05.268
AND LOOK AT ME NOW,

03:05.351 --> 03:07.437
SINGING A SOLO
TO A PACKED HOUSE.

03:07.520 --> 03:09.272
- YOU DO PUT BUTTS IN PEWS,

03:09.355 --> 03:10.940
BUT THAT'S YOU.

03:11.024 --> 03:11.691
THE KIDS HAVE TO FIND
THEIR OWN THING...

03:11.774 --> 03:14.277
WITHOUT US AT NIGHT.

03:14.360 --> 03:15.612
- LOOK, HONEY,
WHEN I WAS A WEEKEND MOM,

03:15.695 --> 03:18.531
I DIDN'T FEEL THE NEED
TO SHAPE THEIR LIVES.

03:18.615 --> 03:20.325
BUT NOW I'M WITH THEM
EVERY DAY,

03:20.408 --> 03:24.495
AND I WANT TO SHARE SOMETHING
THAT MEANS A LOT TO ME.

03:24.579 --> 03:28.082
- OKAY,
BUT I WOULDN'T FORCE IT.

03:28.166 --> 03:30.126
MY PARENTS MADE ME
PLAY THE FLUTE,

03:30.209 --> 03:32.128
THE HARMONICA,
THE VIOLA.

03:32.211 --> 03:33.463
YOU KNOW WHAT I GOT?

03:33.546 --> 03:37.175
- BEAT UP BY KIDS
WHO PLAYED COOL INSTRUMENTS?

03:37.258 --> 03:38.843
- NO, I GOT A CLOSETFUL
OF THROWAWAYS

03:38.927 --> 03:40.511
AND A LOT OF WASTED TIME

03:40.595 --> 03:44.641
I COULD HAVE USED DOING
SOMETHING THAT I'M GOOD AT,

03:44.724 --> 03:48.144
LIKE PERFORMING
A QUADRUPLE BYPASS,

03:48.227 --> 03:49.145
IF YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

03:49.228 --> 03:52.357
- SO YOU'LL SUPPORT ME
ON THIS?

03:52.440 --> 03:53.316
- I SUPPORT YOU.

03:54.984 --> 03:57.028
NOW THAT THAT'S SETTLED,

03:57.111 --> 03:59.697
WE SHOULD, UH...

03:59.781 --> 04:00.782
- HAVE A FAMILY MEETING.

04:00.865 --> 04:02.492
- MM-HMM, YES.

04:02.575 --> 04:04.786
NO!
WHAT?

04:04.869 --> 04:06.204
NO, WE JUST GOT
THE KIDS TO BED.

04:06.287 --> 04:08.456
- HONEY,
THIS CAN'T WAIT.

04:08.539 --> 04:10.375
THE SOONER
WE FINISH A MEETING,

04:10.458 --> 04:14.921
THE SOONER WE DO THAT
SEXY QUADRUPLE OVERPASS THING.

04:16.714 --> 04:17.589
- FAMILY MEETING!

04:17.673 --> 04:18.841
EVERYBODY DOWNSTAIRS!

04:18.925 --> 04:20.677
- [laughing]

04:20.760 --> 04:22.720
- YOU'RE MAKING US
LEARN INSTRUMENTS?

04:22.804 --> 04:24.305
ALL THOSE LESSONS
AND PRACTICE

04:24.389 --> 04:25.974
WILL CUT
INTO MY COLLEGE PREP,

04:26.057 --> 04:28.810
BUT IF YOU'D RATHER I END UP
PLAYING MUSIC IN THE SUBWAY,

04:28.893 --> 04:30.895
THAT'S ANOTHER WAY TO GO.

04:30.979 --> 04:32.772
- LOOK, THIS MEANS A LOT
TO STEPHANIE,

04:32.855 --> 04:33.523
AND WE ARE GONNA
SUPPORT HER.

04:33.606 --> 04:36.609
QUICKLY.

04:36.693 --> 04:37.819
- HOW ABOUT YOU, AARON?

04:37.902 --> 04:38.861
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT INSTRUMENT YOU WANT?

04:38.945 --> 04:40.488
- CAN I PLAY DRUMS?
- DRUMS. DONE.

04:40.571 --> 04:42.240
GABBY, YOU'RE UP.

04:42.323 --> 04:43.700
- I DON'T WANT TO DO THIS.

04:43.783 --> 04:46.077
- AND I DON'T WANT
TO PAY YOUR CELL PHONE BILL.

04:46.160 --> 04:47.036
- KEYBOARD.

04:47.120 --> 04:48.246
- KEYBOARD.
YOU GOT IT.

04:48.329 --> 04:49.163
YOU.

04:49.247 --> 04:51.374
MIDDLE KID.
PICK.

04:51.457 --> 04:55.461
- ACTUALLY, IT'S ALWAYS BEEN
A DREAM OF MINE TO PLAY...

04:55.545 --> 04:58.548
THE HARP.

04:58.631 --> 05:00.216
- SEE?

05:00.299 --> 05:02.343
AND YOU SAID HE DIDN'T HAVE
ANY MUSICAL INTERESTS.

05:02.427 --> 05:03.553
- YOUR DREAM?

05:03.636 --> 05:04.804
NAME ONE HARP PLAYER.

05:04.887 --> 05:06.139
- WHO CARES?
BOY'S GETTING A HARP.

05:06.222 --> 05:07.640
EVERYBODY BACK UPSTAIRS!

05:13.980 --> 05:15.231
- WHAT JUST HAPPENED?

05:15.314 --> 05:16.816
- YOU AGREED
TO LEARN AN INSTRUMENT,

05:16.899 --> 05:19.193
AND I GOT OUT OF IT.

05:19.277 --> 05:22.989
- YOU DIDN'T GET OUT
OF ANYTHING, HARP BOY.

05:23.072 --> 05:24.615
- AND WHERE IS STEPHANIE
GONNA GET A HARP,

05:24.699 --> 05:26.534
STEAL IT
FROM A HOTEL LOBBY?

05:28.161 --> 05:29.787
SHE'S NEVER GONNA
MAKE THIS HAPPEN.

05:29.871 --> 05:31.164
- WELL, GOOD LUCK WITH THAT.

05:31.247 --> 05:33.458
I'M GONNA FIND A PLAN
THAT ACTUALLY WORKS.

05:33.541 --> 05:34.584
- DO WHATEVER YOU WANT.

05:34.667 --> 05:35.585
I'M GONNA STICK
WITH MY PLAN.

05:35.668 --> 05:37.670
AND IT'S FOOLPROOF,
FOOL.

05:37.754 --> 05:39.338
YOU'RE ON YOUR OWN.

05:39.422 --> 05:39.881
AH, KEYBOARD.

05:39.964 --> 05:41.841
ROOKIE MISTAKE.

05:41.924 --> 05:45.803
- YOU'RE NOT GONNA BE SO COCKY
WHEN SHE'S HANDING YOU A HARP.

05:45.887 --> 05:47.597
- BELIEVE ME,

05:47.680 --> 05:50.224
SAINT PETER WILL BE HANDING ME
A HARP BEFORE STEPHANIE DOES.

05:55.229 --> 05:56.272
- [clears throat]

05:56.355 --> 05:58.232
♪ DO, RE, MI, FA,
SO, LA, TI, DO ♪

05:58.316 --> 05:59.317
[drumsticks clacking]

05:59.400 --> 06:01.027
♪ DO, TI, LA, SO,
FA, MI, RE, DO ♪

06:01.110 --> 06:02.862
♪ DO, RE, MI, FA,
SO, LA, TI, DO ♪

06:02.945 --> 06:05.782
♪ DO, TI, LA, SO,
FA, MI, RE, DO ♪

06:05.865 --> 06:07.450
[louder] ♪ DO, RE, MI, FA,
SO, LA, TI, DO ♪

06:07.533 --> 06:10.369
♪ DO, TI, LA, SO,
FA, MI, RE, DO ♪

06:10.453 --> 06:15.041
both:
I'M TRYING TO PRACTICE HERE!

06:15.124 --> 06:17.960
- AARON, I'M GLAD YOU'RE EXCITED
ABOUT YOUR NEW DRUM SET,

06:18.044 --> 06:20.713
BUT UNTIL IT ARRIVES,
I'M A SOLO ACT.

06:20.797 --> 06:22.507
GO PLAY SOMEWHERE ELSE.

06:24.383 --> 06:25.802
[drumsticks clacking]

06:25.885 --> 06:29.555
- OW! OW!

06:29.639 --> 06:32.517
GLAD YOU DIDN'T
GET HIM A TUBA.

06:32.600 --> 06:33.810
- OH, JAMES.

06:33.893 --> 06:36.354
I AM SO SORRY WE HAVEN'T
GOTTEN YOU STARTED YET.

06:36.437 --> 06:37.605
IT'S JUST BEEN
A LITTLE TOUGH

06:37.688 --> 06:39.816
TRYING TO MAKE
THIS WHOLE HARP THING HAPPEN.

06:39.899 --> 06:41.901
- NO RUSH.

06:41.984 --> 06:43.361
YOU'VE GOT THAT BIG SOLO
TO WORRY ABOUT.

06:43.444 --> 06:44.821
MY DREAMS CAN WAIT.

06:44.904 --> 06:48.074
- NO, NO, NO, NO,
THEY CAN'T, AND THEY WON'T.

06:48.157 --> 06:49.325
HERE.

06:49.408 --> 06:51.077
WHY DON'T YOU LOOK
THROUGH THIS HARP CATALOG?

06:51.160 --> 06:51.452
- THAT'S A THING?

06:54.205 --> 06:55.706
I MEAN, YAY.

06:57.708 --> 06:58.751
- AH.

06:58.835 --> 06:59.961
YOU GONNA PRACTICE
AS MUCH AS YOUR SISTER?

07:00.044 --> 07:02.296
SHE'S TAKING TO THE KEYBOARD
LIKE A PRODIGY.

07:02.380 --> 07:03.673
- I KNOW.

07:03.756 --> 07:05.091
I HAD TO PUSH HER AT FIRST,

07:05.174 --> 07:06.759
BUT NOW SHE COMES HOME
FROM SCHOOL,

07:06.843 --> 07:09.595
GOES STRAIGHT TO HER ROOM,
AND PLAYS UNTIL DINNER.

07:09.679 --> 07:13.641
IT'S BEEN A LOT OF HARD WORK,
BUT I AM SO PROUD OF MYSELF.

07:14.225 --> 07:16.102
AND OF GABBY.

07:16.185 --> 07:17.395
- HMM.

07:17.478 --> 07:19.605
I MEAN, CAN YOU BELIEVE
HOW QUICKLY SHE PICKED IT UP?

07:19.689 --> 07:21.983
TOOK HER TWICE AS LONG TO
MEMORIZE MY CREDIT CARD NUMBER,

07:22.066 --> 07:24.652
AND SHE USES THAT
EVERY DAY.

07:24.735 --> 07:26.279
[elegant piano music
playing faintly]

07:26.362 --> 07:26.821
THERE SHE GOES AGAIN.

07:26.904 --> 07:29.240
LISTEN TO THAT.

07:29.323 --> 07:30.658
- [scoffs] I JUST WISH
SHE WASN'T SO SHY ABOUT IT.

07:30.741 --> 07:33.536
I MEAN, I WOULD LOVE
TO WATCH HER DO HER THING,

07:33.619 --> 07:34.871
BUT SHE HASN'T LET ME
IN HER ROOM

07:34.954 --> 07:36.372
SINCE SHE STARTED PRACTICING.

07:36.455 --> 07:38.749
- SHE HASN'T LET ME IN HER ROOM
SINCE WE GAVE HER ONE.

07:39.500 --> 07:41.752
- FOUND IT.
- OH.

07:41.836 --> 07:42.795
- PAGE 12.

07:42.879 --> 07:44.046
- OKAY.

07:44.130 --> 07:45.256
WHOA!

07:45.339 --> 07:46.632
$24,000 FOR A HARP?

07:46.716 --> 07:51.012
- HEY, MUSIC OF THE ANGELS
AIN'T CHEAP.

07:51.095 --> 07:52.680
- BUT WE ARE.
KEEP LOOKING.

07:56.142 --> 07:57.101
[tires squealing]

07:57.185 --> 07:59.312
OH, MAN, NO FAIR!

07:59.395 --> 08:00.271
MY CONTROLLER'S BROKEN.

08:00.354 --> 08:01.731
I KEEP GOING INTO THE RAIL.

08:01.814 --> 08:05.526
- THIS IS WHY THEY
SHOULDN'T LET OLD PEOPLE DRIVE.

08:05.610 --> 08:07.111
- I GOT ONE MOVE LEFT.

08:07.195 --> 08:08.070
HA-HA!

08:08.154 --> 08:10.031
[cackling]

08:10.114 --> 08:11.199
OH-HO!

08:11.282 --> 08:12.617
- EVERY TIME.
- [laughing]

08:12.700 --> 08:14.035
- OH, JAMES.

08:14.118 --> 08:17.663
ANYBODY ORDER A HARP?

08:20.875 --> 08:23.669
- OH, WOW,
YOU FOUND ME A HARP.

08:26.088 --> 08:27.256
BUT I DIDN'T WANT
ONE OF THESE.

08:27.340 --> 08:31.177
I WANTED ONE OF THESE.

08:32.178 --> 08:33.971
- WELL, THIS
IS A PRACTICE HARP.

08:34.054 --> 08:36.474
IT'S WHAT EVERYBODY
LEARNS ON.

08:36.557 --> 08:39.936
- THIS REALLY ISN'T
MY DREAM, BUT FINE.

08:40.019 --> 08:43.438
- I THINK WHAT YOU MEAN TO SAY,
JAMES, IS, "THANK YOU."

08:43.522 --> 08:46.776
- THIS REALLY ISN'T MY DREAM,
BUT THANK YOU.

08:48.027 --> 08:49.695
IT'S A SHAME
YOU CAN'T FIND A TEACHER.

08:49.779 --> 08:52.448
- AH, THAT'S MY OTHER
GREAT NEWS.

08:52.531 --> 08:55.284
I MANAGED TO TRACK ONE DOWN.

08:55.368 --> 08:56.410
- I CAN HONESTLY SAY,

08:56.494 --> 09:00.498
NEVER THOUGHT THIS DAY
WOULD COME.

09:00.581 --> 09:01.624
- THE TEACHER SUGGESTED
YOU SPEND A COUPLE OF HOURS

09:01.707 --> 09:04.919
JUST STRUMMING
TO BUILD UP YOUR CALLUSES.

09:06.128 --> 09:07.713
- I GUESS IT COULDN'T HURT.

09:07.797 --> 09:09.966
- WELL, ACTUALLY,
HE SAID IT MIGHT.

09:10.967 --> 09:13.636
- MM.

09:17.640 --> 09:19.267
- NO PEEKING.

09:19.350 --> 09:20.726
HERE WE GO.

09:20.810 --> 09:21.894
- DRUMS!

09:21.978 --> 09:23.271
CAN I HIT THEM?

09:23.354 --> 09:25.147
- WELL, THE NEIGHBORS
HAVE TO FIND OUT EVENTUALLY.

09:25.231 --> 09:26.565
HAVE AT IT.

09:29.318 --> 09:32.238
[drums and cymbals
clanging raucously]

09:35.950 --> 09:36.409
- YOU WERE RIGHT.

09:36.492 --> 09:37.326
DRUMS WERE FUN.

09:37.410 --> 09:41.831
NOW CAN I TAKE KARATE?

09:41.914 --> 09:43.499
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
"WERE FUN"?

09:43.582 --> 09:46.335
IF YOU LOVE THE DRUMS,
YOU PLAY EVERY DAY.

09:46.419 --> 09:47.712
- WHY?

09:47.795 --> 09:49.839
I LOVE THE ZOO, BUT I WOULDN'T
WANT TO LIVE THERE.

09:51.382 --> 09:52.717
THANKS AGAIN!

09:55.845 --> 09:58.180
- HI, HI, HI.

09:58.264 --> 09:58.889
GOOD.

09:58.973 --> 10:00.766
YOU'RE SITTING DOWN.

10:00.850 --> 10:02.560
YOUR SOLO'S BEEN CANCELED.

10:02.643 --> 10:05.021
IF YOU FEEL
LIKE HITTING SOMETHING,

10:05.104 --> 10:07.356
YOU'RE IN A GOOD SPOT.

10:07.440 --> 10:08.399
- CANCELED?

10:08.482 --> 10:09.692
WHY?

10:09.775 --> 10:13.070
- OLETA BROKE HER PINKIE FINGER
PRACTICING THE ORGAN.

10:13.154 --> 10:14.572
- WELL, I'M NOT SURPRISED.

10:14.655 --> 10:15.698
SHE'S 80 YEARS OLD,

10:15.781 --> 10:17.408
AND SOMEBODY
KEPT YELLING AT HER

10:17.491 --> 10:20.703
TO PUNCH THOSE KEYS
LIKE HER LIFE DEPENDED ON IT.

10:20.786 --> 10:21.954
- EXCUSE ME.

10:22.038 --> 10:25.249
I THINK OSTEOPOROSIS
IS THE CULPRIT.

10:26.167 --> 10:28.336
ANYWAY,
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

10:28.419 --> 10:29.545
WE DON'T HAVE ANYBODY
TO PLAY THE ORGAN.

10:29.628 --> 10:33.382
[ragtime piano music playing]

10:33.466 --> 10:36.510
♪ ♪

10:36.594 --> 10:38.387
- WAIT A MINUTE.

10:38.471 --> 10:40.723
MAYBE WE DO.

10:40.806 --> 10:42.308
- IS THAT GABBY,

10:42.391 --> 10:43.267
YAY BIG?

10:43.351 --> 10:46.604
ATTITUDE,
YAY BIG?

10:46.687 --> 10:48.397
- MOM, THIS IS PERFECT.

10:48.481 --> 10:50.107
I GET TO SING MY SOLO

10:50.191 --> 10:52.818
AND SHOW OFF GABBY
AT THE SAME TIME.

10:52.902 --> 10:54.820
- AND TO THINK,
WE WERE ALMOST TAKEN DOWN

10:54.904 --> 10:58.657
BY AN OLD WOMAN
WHO WOULDN'T DRINK HER MILK.

11:00.659 --> 11:03.704
[ragtime piano music playing]

11:03.788 --> 11:04.789
♪ ♪

11:09.335 --> 11:10.753
[ragtime piano music playing]

11:10.836 --> 11:11.921
[knock at door]

11:12.004 --> 11:17.051
♪ ♪

11:17.134 --> 11:19.637
[music ends]

11:20.679 --> 11:23.891
- IT'S THE GABBY FAN CLUB.

11:23.974 --> 11:24.892
- AND JAMES.

11:26.894 --> 11:28.771
- THAT'S FANTASTIC.

11:28.854 --> 11:32.817
- ALMOST TOO GOOD
TO BE TRUE.

11:32.900 --> 11:35.277
- JUST ANOTHER DAY
OF BEING MUSICALLY ENRICHED,

11:35.361 --> 11:36.529
THANKS TO STEPHANIE.

11:36.612 --> 11:38.781
- WELL,
I HAVE NEWS FOR YOU.

11:38.864 --> 11:41.283
GUESS WHO'S GONNA BE
ACCOMPANYING MY SOLO

11:41.367 --> 11:42.952
WITH THE CHOIR ON SUNDAY.

11:43.035 --> 11:43.619
- [chuckles]

11:43.702 --> 11:46.539
JAMES ON THAT TINY HARP?

11:47.957 --> 11:50.209
- NO, YOU.

11:50.292 --> 11:53.254
- OH, WOW.

11:53.337 --> 11:55.714
I CAN'T DO THAT.

11:55.798 --> 11:58.342
I MEAN--I MEAN, I CAN,

11:58.426 --> 12:00.469
{\an5}BUT YOU GUYS HAVE AN ORGAN,
RIGHT?

12:00.553 --> 12:01.929
PEDALS, PIPES.

12:02.012 --> 12:03.889
- HONEY, NOBODY'S ASKING YOU
TO PLAY THE ORGAN.

12:03.973 --> 12:06.100
JUST BRING YOUR LITTLE KEYBOARD.
PLUG IT IN.

12:08.227 --> 12:10.479
- IT WOULD TAKE TOO MUCH TIME
TO LEARN THE MUSIC.

12:10.563 --> 12:11.981
- OH, PIECE OF CAKE.

12:12.064 --> 12:13.274
IT'S SO MUCH EASIER

12:13.357 --> 12:14.650
THAN THE STUFF
THAT YOU'VE BEEN PLAYING.

12:14.733 --> 12:16.569
I CAN GET YOU
THE SHEET MUSIC TODAY.

12:16.652 --> 12:18.821
- UNLESS THERE'S
SOME OTHER REASON

12:18.904 --> 12:20.072
YOU DON'T WANT TO PLAY.

12:22.616 --> 12:24.034
- NO, I CAN MAKE THIS WORK.

12:24.118 --> 12:26.454
- GOOD.

12:26.537 --> 12:30.124
I CAN CALL THE PRAYER CIRCLE,
TELL THEM THEY CAN STOP.

12:30.207 --> 12:32.042
- THIS IS GONNA BE SO MUCH FUN.

12:32.126 --> 12:33.043
- I KNOW.

12:33.127 --> 12:35.713
- YAY ME
FOR ENCOURAGING YOU.

12:35.796 --> 12:38.507
- [chuckling]

12:38.591 --> 12:39.467
- HMM.

12:39.550 --> 12:40.634
IT'S A MYSTERY.

12:40.718 --> 12:42.678
THE SUDDEN UNEXPLAINED
"TALENT,"

12:42.761 --> 12:44.472
LEARNING SONGS
WITH YOUR "HEADPHONES" ON,

12:44.555 --> 12:47.057
AND PLAYING THEM WELL

12:47.141 --> 12:50.269
BEHIND
A "CLOSED BEDROOM DOOR."

12:52.313 --> 12:54.565
- I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

12:56.442 --> 12:57.693
[door clicks shut]

12:57.776 --> 12:59.695
- TELL ME YOUR SECRET,
AND I PROMISE NOT TO BUST YOU.

12:59.778 --> 13:01.447
- IT'S FOOLPROOF,
FOOL.

13:01.530 --> 13:02.907
YOU'RE ON YOUR OWN.

13:02.990 --> 13:05.493
- DON'T WORRY.
I'LL "FIGURE IT OUT."

13:05.576 --> 13:08.662
- WHY DO YOU KEEP MAKING
THOSE STUPID AIR QUOTES?

13:08.746 --> 13:09.914
- I'M NOT.

13:09.997 --> 13:12.666
MY FINGERS
ARE "MANGLED FROM THE HARP."

13:16.295 --> 13:19.256
- YOU HAVE AN ADJACENT STRING,

13:19.340 --> 13:22.051
WHICH IS TO SAY
IT IS IN CLOSE PROXIMITY

13:22.134 --> 13:23.093
TO THE FIRST STRING,

13:23.177 --> 13:25.387
WHICH THEN MUST BE PLUCKED...

13:25.471 --> 13:26.430
[plucks string]

13:26.514 --> 13:29.016
MINOR SECOND,
NOT A MINOR FIRST--

13:29.099 --> 13:30.809
A COMMON MISTAKE
AMONG NEOPHYTES,

13:30.893 --> 13:33.854
OR NOVICE PLAYERS,
AS IT WERE.

13:33.938 --> 13:37.483
I'VE BUILT INTO MY TECHNIQUE,

13:37.566 --> 13:39.735
WHICH IS NOT DISSIMILAR
TO OTHER TECHNIQUES,

13:39.818 --> 13:42.947
YET STILL MAINTAINS
ITS OWN UNIQUENESS...

13:47.159 --> 13:47.910
WHERE WAS I?

13:50.120 --> 13:51.664
- HOW'S IT GOING?

13:51.747 --> 13:54.750
- DREAM COME TRUE.

13:59.338 --> 14:00.256
[soft piano music]

14:00.339 --> 14:03.509
- ♪ WAS BLIND ♪

14:03.592 --> 14:05.553
♪ BUT NOW ♪

14:05.636 --> 14:10.266
♪ I SEE ♪

14:10.349 --> 14:12.184
IT'S GETTING THERE.

14:12.268 --> 14:15.229
- I THOUGHT IT GOT THERE
TWO HOURS AGO.

14:15.312 --> 14:15.896
- ONE MORE AGAIN?

14:15.980 --> 14:18.524
- SURE, NO PROBLEM.

14:18.607 --> 14:21.986
IT'S JUST THAT I HEARD A LITTLE
CRACKING ON THAT LAST NOTE.

14:22.069 --> 14:23.279
- REALLY?

14:23.362 --> 14:24.405
THEN WE'RE DONE.

14:24.488 --> 14:25.030
ONCE I CRACK,
I CAN'T GO BACK.

14:26.574 --> 14:29.243
- OH, BUMMER.

14:31.203 --> 14:32.913
- HAVE I TOLD YOU
HOW PROUD I AM OF YOU?

14:32.997 --> 14:34.039
- YUP.

14:34.123 --> 14:35.874
I GOT YOUR
"I'M PROUD OF YOU" MUG

14:35.958 --> 14:38.127
AND YOUR "I'M PROUD OF YOU"
TWEETS.

14:38.210 --> 14:38.627
[chuckles]

14:38.711 --> 14:40.588
- #YOURETHEBOMB.

14:40.671 --> 14:41.463
- #RIGHTBACKATYOU.

14:41.547 --> 14:43.424
[both chuckle]

14:43.507 --> 14:44.383
- WELL, DINNER'S SOON.

14:44.466 --> 14:46.176
OH, AND, JAMES,
DON'T FORGET,

14:46.260 --> 14:47.469
YOU STILL HAVE
AN HOUR OF HARP TONIGHT.

14:47.553 --> 14:51.682
PRACTICE MAKES GABBY.

14:54.893 --> 14:57.313
- GABBY, GABBY, GABBY.

14:57.396 --> 14:58.647
I KNOW YOUR SECRET.

14:58.731 --> 15:00.149
TOOK ME A LITTLE WHILE,

15:00.232 --> 15:02.985
BUT I FINALLY
PUT MY FINGER ON IT.

15:03.068 --> 15:05.154
[soft piano music plays]

15:05.237 --> 15:06.447
- YOU'RE ABOUT
TO LOSE THAT FINGER

15:06.530 --> 15:08.574
AND A WHOLE LOT MORE.

15:08.657 --> 15:10.784
- THERE'S ONE THING
I HAVEN'T FIGURED OUT:

15:10.868 --> 15:12.786
HOW'D YOU GET THE SONG
PROGRAMMED TO THE MEMORY CARD

15:12.870 --> 15:14.496
IF YOU CAN'T REALLY PLAY?

15:14.580 --> 15:16.665
- THERE'S A BAND GEEK
WHO'S GOT A CRUSH ON ME.

15:16.749 --> 15:18.334
YOU BETTER NOT RAT ME OUT.

15:18.417 --> 15:21.670
- HEY, I'M NOT
AN UNREASONABLE MAN.

15:21.754 --> 15:23.255
- WHAT DO YOU WANT?

15:23.339 --> 15:24.590
- WHAT HAVE YOU GOT?

15:26.050 --> 15:28.719
- AN "I'M PROUD OF YOU" MUG
AND $5?

15:28.802 --> 15:30.179
- I'LL TAKE THE $5

15:30.262 --> 15:32.097
AND $10 MORE FOR INSULTING ME
WITH THAT MUG.

15:37.936 --> 15:40.022
- A REMINDER
AS THE OFFERING PLATE

15:40.105 --> 15:41.815
IS BEING PASSED AROUND:

15:41.899 --> 15:44.902
THE VEGAN BAKE SALE
WAS A HEARTBREAKING FAILURE.

15:45.444 --> 15:47.655
AND NOW...

15:47.738 --> 15:48.864
OH, YES, SIR,
THEY WOWED YOU

15:48.947 --> 15:52.159
WITH <i> I KNOW</i>
<i>THAT MY REDEEMER LIVED.</i>

15:52.242 --> 15:53.744
AND THEY MOVED YOU WITH...

15:53.827 --> 15:56.538
♪ HOLY SPIRIT,
TRUTH DIVINE ♪

15:56.622 --> 15:57.748
THEIR RENDITION

15:57.831 --> 15:59.917
OF <i> THERE IS A FOUNTAIN</i>
<i>FILLED WITH BLOOD</i>

16:00.000 --> 16:03.796
WENT TO NUMBER ONE
ON THE CHURCH WEBSITE.

16:03.879 --> 16:05.130
OUR CHOIR.

16:05.214 --> 16:06.548
OUR LOVELY SOLOIST,

16:06.632 --> 16:08.258
MS. STEPHANIE PHILLIPS!

16:08.342 --> 16:10.219
MM-HMM.

16:10.302 --> 16:11.387
[applause]

16:11.470 --> 16:13.889
- YOU'RE EMBARRASSING ME,
REVEREND.

16:13.972 --> 16:14.973
HI.

16:15.057 --> 16:16.892
BEFORE WE BEGIN,
I'D LIKE TO ANNOUNCE

16:16.975 --> 16:21.397
THAT OUR USUAL ACCOMPANIST
COULD NOT BE HERE TODAY...

16:21.480 --> 16:24.566
- BRITTLE BONES.

16:24.650 --> 16:27.361
- BUT MY STEPDAUGHTER
HAS GRACIOUSLY AGREED

16:27.444 --> 16:29.488
TO ACCOMPANY US.

16:29.571 --> 16:32.324
THEY SAY IT'S BETTER
TO GIVE THAN TO RECEIVE.

16:32.408 --> 16:34.785
AND I COULDN'T FEEL
MORE REWARDED THAN I DO TODAY

16:34.868 --> 16:38.330
FOR HAVING GIVEN MY STEPCHILDREN
THE GIFT OF MUSIC.

16:38.414 --> 16:40.624
- I'D LIKE TO GIVE
THAT GIFT BACK.

16:42.251 --> 16:44.002
- YOU MAY HAVE NEVER HEARD
AN ANGEL SING,

16:44.086 --> 16:46.797
BUT YOU'RE ABOUT
TO HEAR ONE PLAY--

16:46.880 --> 16:48.632
GABBY PHILLIPS.

16:48.716 --> 16:52.511
[applause]

16:52.594 --> 16:53.762
- I'LL NEVER HAVE
TO TOUCH THAT HARP AGAIN.

16:53.846 --> 16:55.723
- WHAT'S THAT?

16:55.806 --> 16:56.974
- GABBY'S KEYBOARD MEMORY CARD

16:57.057 --> 17:00.102
OR, AS I CALL IT,
THE DAY THE MUSIC DIED.

17:03.856 --> 17:05.773
- OKAY.

17:05.858 --> 17:07.568
[choir humming]

17:07.651 --> 17:13.281
- ♪ AMAZING GRACE ♪

17:13.365 --> 17:14.907
[no music playing]

17:14.992 --> 17:17.411
♪ HOW SWEET ♪

17:17.493 --> 17:18.162
♪ THE SOUND ♪

17:20.998 --> 17:22.833
- CAN WE START AGAIN,
PLEASE?

17:25.377 --> 17:28.630
- ♪ AMAZING GRACE ♪

17:28.714 --> 17:31.633
♪ HOW SWEET ♪

17:31.717 --> 17:32.676
♪ THE SOUND ♪

17:32.760 --> 17:35.053
[hip-hop drumbeat]

17:35.137 --> 17:37.181
♪ THAT SAVED ♪

17:37.264 --> 17:38.891
♪ A WRETCH ♪

17:38.974 --> 17:40.851
♪ LIKE ME ♪

17:40.934 --> 17:42.311
♪ I ONCE WAS LOST,
BUT NOW I'M FOUND ♪

17:42.394 --> 17:45.230
♪ ♪

17:45.314 --> 17:46.231
♪ WHAT ARE WE DOING? ♪

17:46.315 --> 17:47.399
♪ WHAT ARE WE DOING? ♪

17:47.483 --> 17:48.317
♪ WHAT ARE WE DOING? ♪

17:48.400 --> 17:51.320
♪ ♪

17:51.403 --> 17:52.237
[drumbeat ends abruptly]

17:53.906 --> 17:54.823
- THANK YOU.

17:54.907 --> 17:55.824
AMEN.

17:55.908 --> 17:57.034
- GABBY, WHAT THE--

17:57.117 --> 17:57.785
- I'M SO SORRY.
I CAN'T REALLY PLAY.

17:57.868 --> 17:59.995
I'LL BE IN THE CAR.

18:02.581 --> 18:03.999
- UH, SINCE WE FIND OURSELVES

18:04.082 --> 18:07.086
WITH SOME UNEXPECTED TIME
TO FILL,

18:07.169 --> 18:09.046
STOP ME IF YOU HEARD
THIS ONE BEFORE:

18:09.129 --> 18:12.716
ME AND A RABBI,
WE WALK INTO A BAR...

18:14.176 --> 18:16.095
- THAT WAS
THE MOST HUMILIATING THING

18:16.178 --> 18:17.513
THAT HAS EVER HAPPENED TO ME.

18:17.596 --> 18:19.848
- OH, HONEY,
GIVE IT SOME TIME.

18:19.932 --> 18:22.684
SOMETHING MUCH MORE HUMILIATING
WILL COME ALONG.

18:22.768 --> 18:25.062
- IT WAS HORRIBLE.

18:25.145 --> 18:27.356
THIS WHOLE THING
WAS HORRIBLE.

18:27.439 --> 18:28.690
I JUST...

18:28.774 --> 18:29.525
- WHAT?

18:29.608 --> 18:31.610
SHOULD'VE LISTENED TO ME?

18:31.693 --> 18:33.904
- DO YOU REALLY WANT
TO GO THERE RIGHT NOW?

18:33.987 --> 18:34.696
[knock at door]

18:34.780 --> 18:36.657
- STEPHANIE?

18:36.740 --> 18:37.574
- ALL RIGHT,
JUST REMEMBER:

18:37.658 --> 18:38.992
IF YOU KILL HER,

18:39.076 --> 18:40.369
THERE'LL BE NOBODY LEFT
IN THIS HOUSE

18:40.452 --> 18:41.453
WHO CARES ABOUT YOUR SHOES.

18:44.164 --> 18:46.083
- [sighs]

18:46.166 --> 18:47.626
COME IN.

18:50.546 --> 18:52.548
- I JUST WANTED
TO SAY SORRY.

18:52.631 --> 18:54.258
- FOR WHAT,

18:54.341 --> 18:55.300
RUINING MY SOLO,

18:55.384 --> 18:58.011
EMBARRASSING ME
IN FRONT OF MY CHURCH,

18:58.095 --> 19:00.389
LYING TO ME
THIS WHOLE TIME?

19:00.472 --> 19:01.640
- SURE,

19:01.723 --> 19:03.976
ALL THAT.

19:04.059 --> 19:06.687
- YOU DON'T SOUND VERY SORRY.

19:06.770 --> 19:08.063
- THAT'S BECAUSE STEPHANIE

19:08.146 --> 19:10.148
SHOULD BE APOLOGIZING
TO ME TOO.

19:10.232 --> 19:11.525
- FOR WHAT?

19:11.608 --> 19:13.902
- FOR FORCING ME
TO PLAY AN INSTRUMENT,

19:13.986 --> 19:16.071
FOR IGNORING ME WHEN I SAID
I WASN'T INTERESTED,

19:16.154 --> 19:19.616
FOR VOLUNTEERING ME
TO PLAY AT CHURCH.

19:21.994 --> 19:24.163
- OKAY,
MAYBE I CAN SEE THAT.

19:26.748 --> 19:28.500
I'M SORRY.

19:28.584 --> 19:29.501
AND YOUR FATHER'S SORRY TOO.

19:29.585 --> 19:32.796
- HUH?

19:32.880 --> 19:34.089
FOR WHAT,

19:34.173 --> 19:36.258
NOT STOPPING THIS WHOLE THING
BEFORE IT STARTED?

19:36.341 --> 19:37.217
- APOLOGY ACCEPTED.

19:37.301 --> 19:40.804
- NOT WHAT I MEANT,
BUT SURE.

19:40.888 --> 19:42.848
NOW, CAN WE AT LEAST
FINALLY ADMIT

19:42.931 --> 19:45.642
THAT WE DON'T HAVE
MUSICAL KIDS?

19:45.726 --> 19:47.519
[bluesy harmonica music playing]

19:47.603 --> 19:48.979
- WHAT'S THAT?

19:49.062 --> 19:50.439
- MUST BE THE TV.

19:50.522 --> 19:56.194
♪ ♪

19:58.530 --> 20:00.365
- HMM.

20:00.449 --> 20:04.202
♪ ♪

20:07.706 --> 20:10.459
[raucous harmonica music
playing]

20:10.542 --> 20:18.592
♪ ♪

20:21.762 --> 20:25.098
[drums banging]

20:25.182 --> 20:28.185
♪ ♪
